1.title: The Existentialist
1.plot: "Josh" tries to escape his existential existence through online dating, but is flying half way around the globe for a date the answer?

2.title: Dating App Addict
2.plot: When "Sandy" swaps drugs for dating apps he finds himself embroiled in an even seedier world than the one he is trying to escape.

3.title: The Princess and the Bogan
3.plot: When "Maria" downloads a dating app to help break her conservative dating habits she gets more bogan than she bargained for.

4.title: Grindr Surprise
4.plot: "Dale" gets on Grindr with the usual expectations of intimate relations but finds himself on a romantic date that exceeds his expectations enormously.

5.title: Nuttier than Squirrel Poo
5.plot: As an experiment "Drew" gets on Tinder, but finds himself at the end of someone else's experiment.

6.title: Death by Dating App
6.plot: A bet gone out of hand sees "Giancarlo" fly to Venezuela to meet a woman he met online, but is he flying into a trap?

7.title: Menage a Tinder
7.plot: "Kayla", a self-professed "Gaysian" (Gay-Asian) gamer, has an intense and highly sexual online relationship for two years without ever meeting her lover in person.

8.title: The Gaysian Gamer
8.plot: "Kayla", a self-professed "Gaysian" (Gay-Asian) gamer, has an intense and highly sexual online relationship for two years without ever meeting her lover in person.

9.title: Six Months of Celibacy
9.plot: "Tara's" self-imposed period of celibacy is tested when she meets a fireman on Tinder.

10.title: D-Grade Celebrity
10.plot: "Wazza" "hooks up" with women through his misogynistic "online persona", but his "personal brand" is compromised when he finds himself going viral.

imdb.plot outline: No Strings Attached is an original documentary series that peers beneath the covers of the exhilarating and hilariously awkward world of online dating. It is a genre-bending mash-up where documentary, comedy, drama and reality-TV collide. It's Crank Yankers meets Creature Comforts on the set of The Bachelor. This unique and edgy series features a cast of puppets that lip-sync and re-enact real-life audio recordings of dating app users and their stories from around the globe. On the surface, No Strings Attached is an entertaining comedy, but at its heart, it is a study of modern relationships and the surprising and silly things that occur when we're trying to connect with a fellow human being.
